                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" fkcefr="c2" hclass="sense" id="anathema_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" htag="span" hclass="def">a thing or an idea that you hate because it is the opposite of what you believe</span></span><ul class="examples" htag="ul" hclass="examples"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">Racial prejudice is (an) anathema to me.</span></li></ul><span class="topic-g"><span class="prefix">Topics </span><a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/topic/preferences-and-decisions?level=c2" title="Topic preferences-and-decisions"><span class="topic" href="l2:functions:preferences_and_decisions?cefr=c2"><span class="topic_name">Preferences and decisions</span><span class="topic_cefr">c2</span></span></a></span><div class="collapse" htag="div" hclass="collapse"><span class="unbox" id="anathema_unbox_1" unbox="wordorigin"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">early 16th cent.: from ecclesiastical Latin, ‘excommunicated person, excommunication’, from Greek <span class="ei">anathema</span> ‘thing dedicated’, (later) ‘thing devoted to evil, accursed thing’, from <span class="ei">anatithenai</span> ‘to set up’.</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
